    List that stores its six elements in the six members of the class. Unlike ArrayList or Arrays.asList(Object[]) there is no array, only one piece of memory allocated, therefore is very compact and cache and CPU efficient.

    The list is read-only, cannot be modified or re-sized. The elements may be null.

    The list is created via FlatLists.of(java.util.List).
